value.title: Judd Apatow, Rob Reiner accuse Donald Trump of 'mass murder' in separate tweets
value.excerpt: Filmmakers Judd Apatow and Rob Reiner took to Twitter on Tuesday to accuse Donald Trump of dishonesty and murder.

value.title: Gorsuch, Kavanaugh 'didn't really tip' Supreme Court balance, Trump advisers say in new book
value.excerpt: Because both Gorsuch and Kavanaugh replaced Republican-appointed justices, David Bossie and Cory Lewandowski say, a second Trump term in which he may have the chance to replace Democrat-appointed justices could be more impactful.

value.title: Ilhan Omar fires back after Trump's rally attack: 'This is my country'
value.excerpt: Rep. Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., fired back at President Trump on Tuesday night after he told a rally crowd she was lecturing Republicans on how to run the country and referenced her native Somalia.

value.title: McMaster warns Trump plays 'into Putin's hands' with warm remarks about Russian president
value.excerpt: President Trump should be harder on Russian President Vladimir Putin in his public statements, former National Security Adviser H.R. McMaster argued on "The Story" Tuesday.

value.title: Cindy McCain, wife of late GOP senator, is endorsing Joe Biden
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden announced Tuesday that Cindy McCain, the wife of late Republican Sen. John McCain, is endorsing his presidential bid following President Trump’s alleged remarks about U.S. services members as reported by The Atlantic.

value.title: China fumes at Trump’s UN speech, accuses US of spreading 'political virus'
value.excerpt: China on Tuesday responded angrily to President Trump’s speech at the U.N. General Assembly, in which he blamed the communist country for the coronavirus pandemic -- with Beijing accusing Trump of spreading a “political virus.”

value.title: VA cancels 'race cafe' event that allegedly violated Trump's executive order
value.excerpt: The Department of Veterans Affairs told Fox News that it has cancelled an event on race and microaggressions after appearing to defend it as complying with the president's recent executive order on critical race theory.

value.title: Joe Biden blasts Bernie in pitch to Wisconsin voters: 'I beat the socialist'
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Joe Biden appeared to slight his former opponent, Sen. Bernie Sanders, I-Vt., on Monday in an attempt to assuage voters' concerns that he would pursue a socialist agenda.

value.title: Lawrence Jones slams Biden for not releasing Supreme Court list: ‘Swing voters and moderates want to know’
value.excerpt: Joe Biden should release his Supreme Court nominee list but he doesn't want to "box himself in," Fox Nation host Lawrence Jones said.

value.title: Trump: Supreme Court pick to be announced Saturday at White House
value.excerpt: President Trump tweeted Tuesday morning that he'll announce his choice for the Supreme Court this coming Saturday at the White House.

value.title: Mike Pence’s plane forced to return to New Hampshire airport after striking bird

value.title: GOP House candidate Kim Klacik claims voters with ‘Trump syndrome’ won’t admit support for her ‘out loud’
value.excerpt: Maryland GOP congressional candidate Kim Klacik’s campaign has caught fire with the help of her viral ads, but many of her would-be constituents are reluctant to outwardly show their support, she told “Hannity” Monday night.

value.title: Watch Live: Trump Holds A "Great American Comeback" Rally In Swanton, Ohio
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump will hold a campaign rally at Toledo Express Airport in Swanton, Ohio on Monday. The rally is expected to begin at 8:00 pm ET.

value.title: Trump must watch his language to get Americans behind SCOTUS choice, Frank Luntz says

value.title: Biden marks grim coronavirus milestone, says ‘Trump panicked’ on pandemic
value.excerpt: As the national death toll from the coronavirus pandemic passes 200,000 people, Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden cautioned that Americans must avoid “becoming numb to the toll that is taken.”

value.title: Andy McCarthy explains why Arizona Senate election could make or break Trump SCOTUS pick
value.excerpt: The outcome of the Arizona Senate race between Republican Martha McSally and Democrat Mark Kelly could determine whether President Trump's nominee to replace late Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg makes it through the Senate, former federal prosecutor Andy McCarthy told "Bill Hemmer Reports"

value.title: Trump touted that he and McConnell 'have broken every record' with judicial appointments: report
value.excerpt: President Trump touted to journalist Bob Woodward that he and Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell, R-Ky., “have broken every record” when it comes to judicial appointments.

value.title: Biden condemns push to fast track Supreme Court confirmation as 'exercise in raw political power'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden on Sunday made a personal appeal to the handful of Senate Republicans who will determine if President Trump’s pending Supreme Court nominee will go forward.

value.excerpt: Former NFL player Herschel Walker urged BLM supporters to think about what they're promoting and defended President Trump's character.

value.title: AOC warns libs Trump-Biden election a lifestyle changer: ‘There’s no going back to brunch’
value.excerpt: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez has braced her supporters for a very different future than they may have expected -- even if presidential nominee Joe Biden and other Democrats prevail in November.

value.title: Kamala Harris pays tribute to RBG with Supreme Court pic
value.excerpt: Democratic Vice Presidential candidate Kamala Harris paid tribute to the passing of Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsberg Saturday, calling the liberal icon a “titan.”

value.title: Trump calls mail-in voting a scam, says Democrats are setting up election 'mess'

value.title: Trump on whether FBI Director Wray could be replaced: 'We're looking at a lot of different things'
value.excerpt: The president ripped Wray for his comments regarding Russian election interference and Antifa.

value.title: Kosovo gives Trump Order of Freedom for his role in securing deal with Serbia
value.excerpt: Kosovo gave President Trump one of its highest honors on Friday for his role in an historic economic normalization deal with Serbia earlier this month.

value.title: What’s up with Trump and the Hispanic vote?
value.excerpt: Voters may have noticed what’s missing from Trump’s reelection pitch compared to his campaign of four years ago: Immigration.

value.title: Ivanka Trump raises $7.5 million for campaign in Texas, Florida trips
value.excerpt: White House adviser Ivanka Trump raised $7.5 million for her father’s campaign in trips to Texas and Florida over the past week, a Trump aide familiar with fundraising told Fox News.
